<TITLE> MA Taslim takes reins of BFTI </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 13 (bdnews24.com)Professor MA Taslim has taken over as chief executive officer of Bangladesh Foreign Trade Institute, a commerce ministry official said. A public-private partnership, BFTI is overseen by a board of directors chaired by the commerce minister, with the ministry's secretary and the FBCCI president as vice chairpersons. Dr Taslim, who also sits on the board of the central bank and is a member of Bangladesh Better Business Forum, will be on leave from his job as professor of economics at Dhaka University. Taslim, who co-chairs the macroeconomic working group of BBBF, will be at the helm of BFTI until 2010. bdn
